91static CSSValueID valueForRepeatRule(NinePieceImageRule rule)
92{
93 switch (rule) {
94 case NinePieceImageRule::Repeat:
95 return CSSValueRepeat;
96 case NinePieceImageRule::Round:
97 return CSSValueRound;
98 case NinePieceImageRule::Space:
99 return CSSValueSpace;
100 default:
101 return CSSValueStretch;
102 }
103}
104
105static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> valueForImageSliceSide(const Length& length)
106{
107 // These values can be percentages, numbers, or while an animation of mixed types is in progress,
108 // a calculation that combines a percentage and a number.
109 if (length.isPercent())
110 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length.percent(), CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE);
111 if (length.isAuto() || length.isFixed())
112 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length.value(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
113
114 // Calculating the actual length currently in use would require most of the code from RenderBoxModelObject::paintNinePieceImage.
115 // And even if we could do that, it's not clear if that's exactly what we'd want during animation.
116 // FIXME: For now, just return 0.
117 ASSERT(length.isCalculated());
118 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(0, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
119}
120
121static Ref<CSSBorderImageSliceValue> valueForNinePieceImageSlice(const NinePieceImage& image)
122{
123 auto& slices = image.imageSlices();
124
125 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> top = valueForImageSliceSide(slices.top());
126
127 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> right;
128 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> bottom;
129 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> left;
130
131 if (slices.right() == slices.top() && slices.bottom() == slices.top() && slices.left() == slices.top()) {
132 right = top;
133 bottom = top;
134 left = top;
135 } else {
136 right = valueForImageSliceSide(slices.right());
137
138 if (slices.bottom() == slices.top() && slices.right() == slices.left()) {
139 bottom = top;
140 left = right;
141 } else {
142 bottom = valueForImageSliceSide(slices.bottom());
143
144 if (slices.left() == slices.right())
145 left = right;
146 else
147 left = valueForImageSliceSide(slices.left());
148 }
149 }
150
151 auto quad = Quad::create();
152 quad->setTop(WTFMove(top));
153 quad->setRight(WTFMove(right));
154 quad->setBottom(WTFMove(bottom));
155 quad->setLeft(WTFMove(left));
156
157 return CSSBorderImageSliceValue::create(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(WTFMove(quad)), image.fill());
158}
159
160static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> valueForNinePieceImageQuad(const LengthBox& box, const RenderStyle& style)
161{
162 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> top;
163 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> right;
164 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> bottom;
165 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> left;
166
167 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
168
169 if (box.top().isRelative())
170 top = cssValuePool.createValue(box.top().value(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
171 else
172 top = cssValuePool.createValue(box.top(), style);
173
174 if (box.right() == box.top() && box.bottom() == box.top() && box.left() == box.top()) {
175 right = top;
176 bottom = top;
177 left = top;
178 } else {
179 if (box.right().isRelative())
180 right = cssValuePool.createValue(box.right().value(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
181 else
182 right = cssValuePool.createValue(box.right(), style);
183
184 if (box.bottom() == box.top() && box.right() == box.left()) {
185 bottom = top;
186 left = right;
187 } else {
188 if (box.bottom().isRelative())
189 bottom = cssValuePool.createValue(box.bottom().value(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
190 else
191 bottom = cssValuePool.createValue(box.bottom(), style);
192
193 if (box.left() == box.right())
194 left = right;
195 else {
196 if (box.left().isRelative())
197 left = cssValuePool.createValue(box.left().value(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
198 else
199 left = cssValuePool.createValue(box.left(), style);
200 }
201 }
202 }
203
204 auto quad = Quad::create();
205 quad->setTop(WTFMove(top));
206 quad->setRight(WTFMove(right));
207 quad->setBottom(WTFMove(bottom));
208 quad->setLeft(WTFMove(left));
209
210 return cssValuePool.createValue(WTFMove(quad));
211}
212
213static Ref<CSSValue> valueForNinePieceImageRepeat(const NinePieceImage& image)
214{
215 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
216 auto horizontalRepeat = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(valueForRepeatRule(image.horizontalRule()));
217 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalRepeat;
218 if (image.horizontalRule() == image.verticalRule())
219 verticalRepeat = horizontalRepeat.copyRef();
220 else
221 verticalRepeat = cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(valueForRepeatRule(image.verticalRule()));
222 return cssValuePool.createValue(Pair::create(WTFMove(horizontalRepeat), WTFMove(verticalRepeat)));
223}
224
225static Ref<CSSValue> valueForNinePieceImage(const NinePieceImage& image, const RenderStyle& style)
226{
227 if (!image.hasImage())
228 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
229
230 RefPtr<CSSValue> imageValue;
231 if (image.image())
232 imageValue = image.image()->cssValue();
233
234 auto imageSlices = valueForNinePieceImageSlice(image);
235 auto borderSlices = valueForNinePieceImageQuad(image.borderSlices(), style);
236 auto outset = valueForNinePieceImageQuad(image.outset(), style);
237 auto repeat = valueForNinePieceImageRepeat(image);
238 return createBorderImageValue(WTFMove(imageValue), WTFMove(imageSlices), WTFMove(borderSlices), WTFMove(outset), WTFMove(repeat));
239}

241inline static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> zoomAdjustedPixelValue(double value, const RenderStyle& style)
242{
243 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(adjustFloatForAbsoluteZoom(value, style), CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
244}
245
246inline static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> zoomAdjustedNumberValue(double value, const RenderStyle& style)
247{
248 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(value / style.effectiveZoom(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
249}
250
251static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(const Length& length, const RenderStyle& style)
252{
253 if (length.isFixed())
254 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(length.value(), style);
255 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length, style);
256}
257
258static Ref<CSSValue> valueForReflection(const StyleReflection* reflection, const RenderStyle& style)
259{
260 if (!reflection)
261 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
262
263 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> offset;
264 if (reflection->offset().isPercentOrCalculated())
265 offset = CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(reflection->offset().percent(), CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE);
266 else
267 offset = zoomAdjustedPixelValue(reflection->offset().value(), style);
268
269 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> direction;
270 switch (reflection->direction()) {
271 case ReflectionDirection::Below:
272 direction = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueBelow);
273 break;
274 case ReflectionDirection::Above:
275 direction = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAbove);
276 break;
277 case ReflectionDirection::Left:
278 direction = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLeft);
279 break;
280 case ReflectionDirection::Right:
281 direction = CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRight);
282 break;
283 }
284
285 return CSSReflectValue::create(direction.releaseNonNull(), offset.releaseNonNull(), valueForNinePieceImage(reflection->mask(), style));
286}
287
288static Ref<CSSValueList> createPositionListForLayer(CSSPropertyID propertyID, const FillLayer& layer, const RenderStyle& style)
289{
290 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
291 if (layer.isBackgroundXOriginSet() && layer.backgroundXOrigin() != Edge::Left) {
292 ASSERT_UNUSED(propertyID, propertyID == CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition || propertyID == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPosition);
293 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(layer.backgroundXOrigin()));
294 }
295 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(layer.xPosition(), style));
296 if (layer.isBackgroundYOriginSet() && layer.backgroundYOrigin() != Edge::Top) {
297 ASSERT(propertyID == CSSPropertyBackgroundPosition || propertyID == CSSPropertyWebkitMaskPosition);
298 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(layer.backgroundYOrigin()));
299 }
300 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(layer.yPosition(), style));
301 return list;
302}
303
304static Length getOffsetComputedLength(const RenderStyle& style, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
305{
306 // If specified as a length, the corresponding absolute length; if specified as
307 // a percentage, the specified value; otherwise, 'auto'. Hence, we can just
308 // return the value in the style.
309 //
310 // See http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/cascade.html#computed-value
311 switch (propertyID) {
312 case CSSPropertyLeft:
313 return style.left();
314 case CSSPropertyRight:
315 return style.right();
316 case CSSPropertyTop:
317 return style.top();
318 case CSSPropertyBottom:
319 return style.bottom();
320 default:
321 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
322 }
323
324 return { };
325}
326
327static LayoutUnit getOffsetUsedStyleRelative(RenderBox& box, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
328{
329 // For relatively positioned boxes, the offset is with respect to the top edges
330 // of the box itself. This ties together top/bottom and left/right to be
331 // opposites of each other.
332 //
333 // See http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/visuren.html#relative-positioning
334 //
335 // Specifically;
336 // Since boxes are not split or stretched as a result of 'left' or
337 // 'right', the used values are always: left = -right.
338 // and
339 // Since boxes are not split or stretched as a result of 'top' or
340 // 'bottom', the used values are always: top = -bottom.
341 switch (propertyID) {
342 case CSSPropertyTop:
343 return box.relativePositionOffset().height();
344 case CSSPropertyBottom:
345 return -(box.relativePositionOffset().height());
346 case CSSPropertyLeft:
347 return box.relativePositionOffset().width();
348 case CSSPropertyRight:
349 return -(box.relativePositionOffset().width());
350 default:
351 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
352 }
353
354 return 0;
355}
356
357static LayoutUnit getOffsetUsedStyleOutOfFlowPositioned(RenderBlock& container, RenderBox& box, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
358{
359 // For out-of-flow positioned boxes, the offset is how far an box's margin
360 // edge is offset below the edge of the box's containing block.
361 // See http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/visuren.html#position-props
362
363 // Margins are included in offsetTop/offsetLeft so we need to remove them here.
364 switch (propertyID) {
365 case CSSPropertyTop:
366 return box.offsetTop() - box.marginTop();
367 case CSSPropertyBottom:
368 return container.clientHeight() - (box.offsetTop() + box.offsetHeight()) - box.marginBottom();
369 case CSSPropertyLeft:
370 return box.offsetLeft() - box.marginLeft();
371 case CSSPropertyRight:
372 return container.clientWidth() - (box.offsetLeft() + box.offsetWidth()) - box.marginRight();
373 default:
374 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
375 }
376
377 return 0;
378}
379
380static RefPtr<CSSValue> positionOffsetValue(const RenderStyle& style, CSSPropertyID propertyID, RenderObject* renderer)
381{
382 auto offset = getOffsetComputedLength(style, propertyID);
383
384 // If the element is not displayed; return the "computed value".
385 if (!renderer || !renderer->isBox())
386 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(offset, style);
387
388 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer);
389 auto* containingBlock = box.containingBlock();
390
391 // Resolve a "computed value" percentage if the element is positioned.
392 if (containingBlock && offset.isPercentOrCalculated() && box.isPositioned()) {
393 bool isVerticalProperty;
394 if (propertyID == CSSPropertyTop || propertyID == CSSPropertyBottom)
395 isVerticalProperty = true;
396 else {
397 ASSERT(propertyID == CSSPropertyLeft || propertyID == CSSPropertyRight);
398 isVerticalProperty = false;
399 }
400 LayoutUnit containingBlockSize;
401 if (box.isStickilyPositioned()) {
402 auto& enclosingClippingBox = box.enclosingClippingBoxForStickyPosition();
403 if (isVerticalProperty == enclosingClippingBox.isHorizontalWritingMode())
404 containingBlockSize = enclosingClippingBox.contentLogicalHeight();
405 else
406 containingBlockSize = enclosingClippingBox.contentLogicalWidth();
407 } else {
408 if (isVerticalProperty == containingBlock->isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
409 containingBlockSize = box.isOutOfFlowPositioned()
410 ? box.containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(*containingBlock, false)
411 : box.containingBlockLogicalHeightForContent(ExcludeMarginBorderPadding);
412 } else {
413 containingBlockSize = box.isOutOfFlowPositioned()
414 ? box.containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(*containingBlock, nullptr, false)
415 : box.containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent();
416 }
417 }
418 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(floatValueForLength(offset, containingBlockSize), style);
419 }
420
421 // Return a "computed value" length.
422 if (!offset.isAuto())
423 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(offset, style);
424
425 // The property won't be overconstrained if its computed value is "auto", so the "used value" can be returned.
426 if (box.isRelativelyPositioned())
427 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(getOffsetUsedStyleRelative(box, propertyID), style);
428
429 if (containingBlock && box.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
430 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(getOffsetUsedStyleOutOfFlowPositioned(*containingBlock, box, propertyID), style);
431
432 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
433}

435Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> ComputedStyleExtractor::currentColorOrValidColor(const RenderStyle* style, const Color& color) const
436{
437 // This function does NOT look at visited information, so that computed style doesn't expose that.
438 if (!color.isValid())
439 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createColorValue(style->color());
440 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createColorValue(color);
441}

443static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> percentageOrZoomAdjustedValue(Length length, const RenderStyle& style)
444{
445 if (length.isPercent())
446 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length.percent(), CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE);
447
448 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(length, style);
449}
450
451static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> autoOrZoomAdjustedValue(Length length, const RenderStyle& style)
452{
453 if (length.isAuto())
454 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
455
456 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(length, style);
457}

459static Ref<CSSValueList> borderRadiusCornerValues(const LengthSize& radius, const RenderStyle& style)
460{
461 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
462 list->append(percentageOrZoomAdjustedValue(radius.width, style));
463 list->append(percentageOrZoomAdjustedValue(radius.height, style));
464 return list;
465}
466
467static Ref<CSSValue> valueForQuotes(const QuotesData* quotes)
468{
469 if (!quotes)
470 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
471 unsigned size = quotes->size();
472 if (!size)
473 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
474 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
475 for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
476 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(quotes->openQuote(i), CSSUnitType::CSS_STRING));
477 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(quotes->closeQuote(i), CSSUnitType::CSS_STRING));
478 }
479 return list;
480}
481
482static Ref<CSSValue> borderRadiusCornerValue(const LengthSize& radius, const RenderStyle& style)
483{
484 if (radius.width == radius.height)
485 return percentageOrZoomAdjustedValue(radius.width, style);
486 return borderRadiusCornerValues(radius, style);
487}
488
489static Ref<CSSValueList> borderRadiusShorthandValue(const RenderStyle& style)
490{
491 auto list = CSSValueList::createSlashSeparated();
492 bool showHorizontalBottomLeft = style.borderTopRightRadius().width != style.borderBottomLeftRadius().width;
493 bool showHorizontalBottomRight = showHorizontalBottomLeft || (style.borderBottomRightRadius().width != style.borderTopLeftRadius().width);
494 bool showHorizontalTopRight = showHorizontalBottomRight || (style.borderTopRightRadius().width != style.borderTopLeftRadius().width);
495
496 bool showVerticalBottomLeft = style.borderTopRightRadius().height != style.borderBottomLeftRadius().height;
497 bool showVerticalBottomRight = showVerticalBottomLeft || (style.borderBottomRightRadius().height != style.borderTopLeftRadius().height);
498 bool showVerticalTopRight = showVerticalBottomRight || (style.borderTopRightRadius().height != style.borderTopLeftRadius().height);
499
500 auto topLeftRadius = borderRadiusCornerValues(style.borderTopLeftRadius(), style);
501 auto topRightRadius = borderRadiusCornerValues(style.borderTopRightRadius(), style);
502 auto bottomRightRadius = borderRadiusCornerValues(style.borderBottomRightRadius(), style);
503 auto bottomLeftRadius = borderRadiusCornerValues(style.borderBottomLeftRadius(), style);
504
505 auto horizontalRadii = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
506 horizontalRadii->append(*topLeftRadius->item(0));
507 if (showHorizontalTopRight)
508 horizontalRadii->append(*topRightRadius->item(0));
509 if (showHorizontalBottomRight)
510 horizontalRadii->append(*bottomRightRadius->item(0));
511 if (showHorizontalBottomLeft)
512 horizontalRadii->append(*bottomLeftRadius->item(0));
513
514 list->append(WTFMove(horizontalRadii));
515
516 auto verticalRadiiList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
517 verticalRadiiList->append(*topLeftRadius->item(1));
518 if (showVerticalTopRight)
519 verticalRadiiList->append(*topRightRadius->item(1));
520 if (showVerticalBottomRight)
521 verticalRadiiList->append(*bottomRightRadius->item(1));
522 if (showVerticalBottomLeft)
523 verticalRadiiList->append(*bottomLeftRadius->item(1));
524
525 if (!verticalRadiiList->equals(downcast<CSSValueList>(*list->item(0))))
526 list->append(WTFMove(verticalRadiiList));
527
528 return list;
529}

531static LayoutRect sizingBox(RenderObject& renderer)
532{
533 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer))
534 return LayoutRect();
535
536 auto& box = downcast<RenderBox>(renderer);
537 return box.style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::BorderBox ? box.borderBoxRect() : box.computedCSSContentBoxRect();
538}
539
540static Ref<CSSFunctionValue> matrixTransformValue(const TransformationMatrix& transform, const RenderStyle& style)
541{
542 RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> transformValue;
543 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
544 if (transform.isAffine()) {
545 transformValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueMatrix);
546
547 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.a(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
548 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.b(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
549 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.c(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
550 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.d(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
551 transformValue->append(zoomAdjustedNumberValue(transform.e(), style));
552 transformValue->append(zoomAdjustedNumberValue(transform.f(), style));
553 } else {
554 transformValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueMatrix3d);
555
556 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m11(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
557 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m12(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
558 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m13(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
559 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m14(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
560
561 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m21(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
562 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m22(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
563 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m23(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
564 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m24(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
565
566 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m31(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
567 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m32(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
568 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m33(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
569 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m34(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
570
571 transformValue->append(zoomAdjustedNumberValue(transform.m41(), style));
572 transformValue->append(zoomAdjustedNumberValue(transform.m42(), style));
573 transformValue->append(zoomAdjustedNumberValue(transform.m43(), style));
574 transformValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(transform.m44(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
575 }
576
577 return transformValue.releaseNonNull();
578}
579
580static bool rendererCanBeTransformed(RenderObject* renderer)
581{
582 // Inline renderers do not support transforms.
583 return renderer && !is<RenderInline>(*renderer);
584}
585
586static Ref<CSSValue> computedTransform(RenderObject* renderer, const RenderStyle& style)
587{
588 if (!rendererCanBeTransformed(renderer) || !style.hasTransform())
589 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
590
591 FloatRect pixelSnappedRect;
592 if (is<RenderBox>(*renderer))
593 pixelSnappedRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).borderBoxRect(), renderer->document().deviceScaleFactor());
594
595 TransformationMatrix transform;
596 style.applyTransform(transform, pixelSnappedRect, { });
597 // Note that this does not flatten to an affine transform if ENABLE(3D_TRANSFORMS) is off, by design.
598
599 // FIXME: Need to print out individual functions (https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=23924)
600 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
601 list->append(matrixTransformValue(transform, style));
602 return list;
603}
604
605static Ref<CSSValue> computedTranslate(RenderObject* renderer, const RenderStyle& style)
606{
607 auto* translate = style.translate();
608 if (!translate || !rendererCanBeTransformed(renderer) || translate->isIdentity())
609 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
610
611 FloatRect pixelSnappedRect;
612 if (is<RenderBox>(*renderer))
613 pixelSnappedRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).borderBoxRect(), renderer->document().deviceScaleFactor());
614
615 TransformationMatrix transform;
616 translate->apply(transform, pixelSnappedRect.size());
617
618 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
619 if (transform.isAffine()) {
620 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValue(transform.e(), style));
621 if (transform.f())
622 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValue(transform.f(), style));
623 } else {
624 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValue(transform.m41(), style));
625 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValue(transform.m42(), style));
626 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValue(transform.m43(), style));
627 }
628
629 return list;
630}
631
632static Ref<CSSValue> computedScale(RenderObject* renderer, const RenderStyle& style)
633{
634 auto* scale = style.scale();
635 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
636 if (!scale || !rendererCanBeTransformed(renderer) || scale->isIdentity())
637 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
638
639 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
640 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(scale->x(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
641 if (scale->z() != 1) {
642 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(scale->y(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
643 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(scale->z(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
644 } else if (scale->x() != scale->y())
645 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(scale->y(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
646 return list;
647}
648
649static Ref<CSSValue> computedRotate(RenderObject* renderer, const RenderStyle& style)
650{
651 auto* rotate = style.rotate();
652 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
653 if (!rotate || !rendererCanBeTransformed(renderer) || rotate->isIdentity())
654 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
655
656 if (!rotate->is3DOperation() || (!rotate->x() && !rotate->y() && rotate->z()))
657 return cssValuePool.createValue(rotate->angle(), CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG);
658
659 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
660
661 if (rotate->x() && !rotate->y() && !rotate->z())
662 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueX));
663 else if (!rotate->x() && rotate->y() && !rotate->z())
664 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueY));
665 else {
666 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(rotate->x(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
667 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(rotate->y(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
668 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(rotate->z(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
669 }
670
671 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(rotate->angle(), CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG));
672
673 return list;
674}
675
676static inline Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> adjustLengthForZoom(double length, const RenderStyle& style, AdjustPixelValuesForComputedStyle adjust)
677{
678 return adjust == AdjustPixelValues ? zoomAdjustedPixelValue(length, style) : CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length, CSSUnitType::CSS_PX);
679}
680
681static inline Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> adjustLengthForZoom(const Length& length, const RenderStyle& style, AdjustPixelValuesForComputedStyle adjust)
682{
683 return adjust == AdjustPixelValues ? zoomAdjustedPixelValue(length.value(), style) : CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(length);
684}
685
686Ref<CSSValue> ComputedStyleExtractor::valueForShadow(const ShadowData* shadow, CSSPropertyID propertyID, const RenderStyle& style, AdjustPixelValuesForComputedStyle adjust)
687{
688 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
689 if (!shadow)
690 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
691
692 auto list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
693 for (const ShadowData* currShadowData = shadow; currShadowData; currShadowData = currShadowData->next()) {
694 auto x = adjustLengthForZoom(currShadowData->x(), style, adjust);
695 auto y = adjustLengthForZoom(currShadowData->y(), style, adjust);
696 auto blur = adjustLengthForZoom(currShadowData->radius(), style, adjust);
697 auto spread = propertyID == CSSPropertyTextShadow ? RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue>() : adjustLengthForZoom(currShadowData->spread(), style, adjust);
698 auto style = propertyID == CSSPropertyTextShadow || currShadowData->style() == ShadowStyle::Normal ? RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue>() : cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueInset);
699 auto color = cssValuePool.createColorValue(currShadowData->color());
700 list->prepend(CSSShadowValue::create(WTFMove(x), WTFMove(y), WTFMove(blur), WTFMove(spread), WTFMove(style), WTFMove(color)));
701 }
702 return list;
703}
704
705Ref<CSSValue> ComputedStyleExtractor::valueForFilter(const RenderStyle& style, const FilterOperations& filterOperations, AdjustPixelValuesForComputedStyle adjust)
706{
707 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
708 if (filterOperations.operations().isEmpty())
709 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
710
711 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
712
713 Vector<RefPtr<FilterOperation>>::const_iterator end = filterOperations.operations().end();
714 for (Vector<RefPtr<FilterOperation>>::const_iterator it = filterOperations.operations().begin(); it != end; ++it) {
715 FilterOperation& filterOperation = **it;
716
717 if (filterOperation.type() == FilterOperation::REFERENCE) {
718 ReferenceFilterOperation& referenceOperation = downcast<ReferenceFilterOperation>(filterOperation);
719 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(referenceOperation.url(), CSSUnitType::CSS_URI));
720 } else {
721 RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> filterValue;
722 switch (filterOperation.type()) {
723 case FilterOperation::GRAYSCALE: {
724 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueGrayscale);
725 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicColorMatrixFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
726 break;
727 }
728 case FilterOperation::SEPIA: {
729 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueSepia);
730 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicColorMatrixFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
731 break;
732 }
733 case FilterOperation::SATURATE: {
734 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueSaturate);
735 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicColorMatrixFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
736 break;
737 }
738 case FilterOperation::HUE_ROTATE: {
739 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueHueRotate);
740 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicColorMatrixFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG));
741 break;
742 }
743 case FilterOperation::INVERT: {
744 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueInvert);
745 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicComponentTransferFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
746 break;
747 }
748 case FilterOperation::APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS: {
749 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueAppleInvertLightness);
750 break;
751 }
752 case FilterOperation::OPACITY: {
753 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueOpacity);
754 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicComponentTransferFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
755 break;
756 }
757 case FilterOperation::BRIGHTNESS: {
758 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueBrightness);
759 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicComponentTransferFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
760 break;
761 }
762 case FilterOperation::CONTRAST: {
763 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueContrast);
764 filterValue->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<BasicComponentTransferFilterOperation>(filterOperation).amount(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
765 break;
766 }
767 case FilterOperation::BLUR: {
768 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueBlur);
769 filterValue->append(adjustLengthForZoom(downcast<BlurFilterOperation>(filterOperation).stdDeviation(), style, adjust));
770 break;
771 }
772 case FilterOperation::DROP_SHADOW: {
773 DropShadowFilterOperation& dropShadowOperation = downcast<DropShadowFilterOperation>(filterOperation);
774 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueDropShadow);
775 // We want our computed style to look like that of a text shadow (has neither spread nor inset style).
776 ShadowData shadowData = ShadowData(dropShadowOperation.location(), dropShadowOperation.stdDeviation(), 0, ShadowStyle::Normal, false, dropShadowOperation.color());
777 filterValue->append(valueForShadow(&shadowData, CSSPropertyTextShadow, style, adjust));
778 break;
779 }
780 default:
781 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
782 filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueInvalid);
783 break;
784 }
785 list->append(filterValue.releaseNonNull());
786 }
787 }
788 return list;
789}
790
791static Ref<CSSValue> specifiedValueForGridTrackBreadth(const GridLength& trackBreadth, const RenderStyle& style)
792{
793 if (!trackBreadth.isLength())
794 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(trackBreadth.flex(), CSSUnitType::CSS_FR);
795
796 const Length& trackBreadthLength = trackBreadth.length();
797 if (trackBreadthLength.isAuto())
798 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
799 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(trackBreadthLength, style);
800}
801
802static Ref<CSSValue> specifiedValueForGridTrackSize(const GridTrackSize& trackSize, const RenderStyle& style)
803{
804 switch (trackSize.type()) {
805 case LengthTrackSizing:
806 return specifiedValueForGridTrackBreadth(trackSize.minTrackBreadth(), style);
807 case FitContentTrackSizing: {
808 auto fitContentTrackSize = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueFitContent);
809 fitContentTrackSize->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(trackSize.fitContentTrackBreadth().length(), style));
810 return fitContentTrackSize;
811 }
812 default:
813 ASSERT(trackSize.type() == MinMaxTrackSizing);
814 if (trackSize.minTrackBreadth().isAuto() && trackSize.maxTrackBreadth().isFlex())
815 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(trackSize.maxTrackBreadth().flex(), CSSUnitType::CSS_FR);
816
817 auto minMaxTrackBreadths = CSSFunctionValue::create(CSSValueMinmax);
818 minMaxTrackBreadths->append(specifiedValueForGridTrackBreadth(trackSize.minTrackBreadth(), style));
819 minMaxTrackBreadths->append(specifiedValueForGridTrackBreadth(trackSize.maxTrackBreadth(), style));
820 return minMaxTrackBreadths;
821 }
822}

824class OrderedNamedLinesCollector {
825 WTF_MAKE_NONCOPYABLE(OrderedNamedLinesCollector);
826public:
827 OrderedNamedLinesCollector(const RenderStyle& style, bool isRowAxis)
828 : m_orderedNamedGridLines(isRowAxis ? style.orderedNamedGridColumnLines() : style.orderedNamedGridRowLines())
829 , m_orderedNamedAutoRepeatGridLines(isRowAxis ? style.autoRepeatOrderedNamedGridColumnLines() : style.autoRepeatOrderedNamedGridRowLines())
830 {
831 }
832 virtual ~OrderedNamedLinesCollector() = default;
833
834 bool isEmpty() const { return m_orderedNamedGridLines.isEmpty() && m_orderedNamedAutoRepeatGridLines.isEmpty(); }
835 virtual void collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue&, unsigned index) const;
836
837protected:
838
839 enum NamedLinesType { NamedLines, AutoRepeatNamedLines };
840 void appendLines(CSSGridLineNamesValue&, unsigned index, NamedLinesType) const;
841
842 const OrderedNamedGridLinesMap& m_orderedNamedGridLines;
843 const OrderedNamedGridLinesMap& m_orderedNamedAutoRepeatGridLines;
844};
845
846class OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInsideRepeat : public OrderedNamedLinesCollector {
847public:
848 OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInsideRepeat(const RenderStyle& style, bool isRowAxis)
849 : OrderedNamedLinesCollector(style, isRowAxis)
850 {
851 }
852
853 void collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue&, unsigned index) const override;
854};
855
856class OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInGridLayout : public OrderedNamedLinesCollector {
857public:
858 OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInGridLayout(const RenderStyle& style, bool isRowAxis, unsigned autoRepeatTracksCount, unsigned autoRepeatTrackListLength)
859 : OrderedNamedLinesCollector(style, isRowAxis)
860 , m_insertionPoint(isRowAxis ? style.gridAutoRepeatColumnsInsertionPoint() : style.gridAutoRepeatRowsInsertionPoint())
861 , m_autoRepeatTotalTracks(autoRepeatTracksCount)
862 , m_autoRepeatTrackListLength(autoRepeatTrackListLength)
863 {
864 }
865
866 void collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue&, unsigned index) const override;
867
868private:
869 unsigned m_insertionPoint;
870 unsigned m_autoRepeatTotalTracks;
871 unsigned m_autoRepeatTrackListLength;
872};
873
874void OrderedNamedLinesCollector::appendLines(CSSGridLineNamesValue& lineNamesValue, unsigned index, NamedLinesType type) const
875{
876 auto iter = type == NamedLines ? m_orderedNamedGridLines.find(index) : m_orderedNamedAutoRepeatGridLines.find(index);
877 auto endIter = type == NamedLines ? m_orderedNamedGridLines.end() : m_orderedNamedAutoRepeatGridLines.end();
878 if (iter == endIter)
879 return;
880
881 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
882 for (const auto& lineName : iter->value)
883 lineNamesValue.append(cssValuePool.createCustomIdent(lineName));
884}
885
886void OrderedNamedLinesCollector::collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue& lineNamesValue, unsigned i) const
887{
888 ASSERT(!isEmpty());
889 appendLines(lineNamesValue, i, NamedLines);
890}
891
892void OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInsideRepeat::collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue& lineNamesValue, unsigned i) const
893{
894 ASSERT(!isEmpty());
895 appendLines(lineNamesValue, i, AutoRepeatNamedLines);
896}
897
898void OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInGridLayout::collectLineNamesForIndex(CSSGridLineNamesValue& lineNamesValue, unsigned i) const
899{
900 ASSERT(!isEmpty());
901 if (!m_autoRepeatTrackListLength || i < m_insertionPoint) {
902 appendLines(lineNamesValue, i, NamedLines);
903 return;
904 }
905
906 ASSERT(m_autoRepeatTotalTracks);
907
908 if (i > m_insertionPoint + m_autoRepeatTotalTracks) {
909 appendLines(lineNamesValue, i - (m_autoRepeatTotalTracks - 1), NamedLines);
910 return;
911 }
912
913 if (i == m_insertionPoint) {
914 appendLines(lineNamesValue, i, NamedLines);
915 appendLines(lineNamesValue, 0, AutoRepeatNamedLines);
916 return;
917 }
918
919 if (i == m_insertionPoint + m_autoRepeatTotalTracks) {
920 appendLines(lineNamesValue, m_autoRepeatTrackListLength, AutoRepeatNamedLines);
921 appendLines(lineNamesValue, m_insertionPoint + 1, NamedLines);
922 return;
923 }
924
925 unsigned autoRepeatIndexInFirstRepetition = (i - m_insertionPoint) % m_autoRepeatTrackListLength;
926 if (!autoRepeatIndexInFirstRepetition && i > m_insertionPoint)
927 appendLines(lineNamesValue, m_autoRepeatTrackListLength, AutoRepeatNamedLines);
928 appendLines(lineNamesValue, autoRepeatIndexInFirstRepetition, AutoRepeatNamedLines);
929}
930
931static void addValuesForNamedGridLinesAtIndex(OrderedNamedLinesCollector& collector, unsigned i, CSSValueList& list)
932{
933 if (collector.isEmpty())
934 return;
935
936 auto lineNames = CSSGridLineNamesValue::create();
937 collector.collectLineNamesForIndex(lineNames.get(), i);
938 if (lineNames->length())
939 list.append(WTFMove(lineNames));
940}

942static Ref<CSSValueList> valueForGridTrackSizeList(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, const RenderStyle& style)
943{
944 auto& autoTrackSizes = direction == ForColumns ? style.gridAutoColumns() : style.gridAutoRows();
945
946 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
947 for (auto& trackSize : autoTrackSizes)
948 list->append(specifiedValueForGridTrackSize(trackSize, style));
949 return list;
950}
951
952template <typename T, typename F>
953void populateGridTrackList(CSSValueList& list, OrderedNamedLinesCollector& collector, const Vector<T>& tracks, F getTrackSize, int start, int end, int offset = 0)
954{
955 ASSERT(0 <= start);
956 ASSERT(start <= end);
957 ASSERT(static_cast<unsigned>(end) <= tracks.size());
958 for (int i = start; i < end; ++i) {
959 if (i + offset >= 0)
960 addValuesForNamedGridLinesAtIndex(collector, i + offset, list);
961 list.append(getTrackSize(tracks[i]));
962 }
963 if (end + offset >= 0)
964 addValuesForNamedGridLinesAtIndex(collector, end + offset, list);
965}
966
967template <typename T, typename F>
968void populateGridTrackList(CSSValueList& list, OrderedNamedLinesCollector& collector, const Vector<T>& tracks, F getTrackSize, int offset = 0)
969{
970 populateGridTrackList<T>(list, collector, tracks, getTrackSize, 0, tracks.size(), offset);
971}
972
973static Ref<CSSValue> valueForGridTrackList(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, RenderObject* renderer, const RenderStyle& style)
974{
975 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
976 bool isRenderGrid = is<RenderGrid>(renderer);
977 auto& trackSizes = isRowAxis ? style.gridColumns() : style.gridRows();
978 auto& autoRepeatTrackSizes = isRowAxis ? style.gridAutoRepeatColumns() : style.gridAutoRepeatRows();
979
980 // Handle the 'none' case.
981 bool trackListIsEmpty = trackSizes.isEmpty() && autoRepeatTrackSizes.isEmpty();
982 if (isRenderGrid && trackListIsEmpty) {
983 // For grids we should consider every listed track, whether implicitly or explicitly
984 // created. Empty grids have a sole grid line per axis.
985 auto& grid = downcast<RenderGrid>(*renderer);
986 auto& positions = isRowAxis ? grid.columnPositions() : grid.rowPositions();
987 trackListIsEmpty = positions.size() == 1;
988 }
989
990 if (trackListIsEmpty)
991 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
992
993 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
994
995 // If the element is a grid container, the resolved value is the used value,
996 // specifying track sizes in pixels and expanding the repeat() notation.
997 if (isRenderGrid) {
998 auto* grid = downcast<RenderGrid>(renderer);
999 OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInGridLayout collector(style, isRowAxis, grid->autoRepeatCountForDirection(direction), autoRepeatTrackSizes.size());
1000 // Named grid line indices are relative to the explicit grid, but we are including all tracks.
1001 // So we need to subtract the number of leading implicit tracks in order to get the proper line index.
1002 int offset = -grid->explicitGridStartForDirection(direction);
1003 populateGridTrackList(list.get(), collector, grid->trackSizesForComputedStyle(direction), [&](const LayoutUnit& v) {
1004 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(v, style);
1005 }, offset);
1006 return list;
1007 }
1008
1009 // Otherwise, the resolved value is the computed value, preserving repeat().
1010 OrderedNamedLinesCollector collector(style, isRowAxis);
1011 auto getTrackSize = [&](const GridTrackSize& v) {
1012 return specifiedValueForGridTrackSize(v, style);
1013 };
1014
1015 if (autoRepeatTrackSizes.isEmpty()) {
1016 // If there's no auto repeat(), just add all the line names and track sizes.
1017 populateGridTrackList(list.get(), collector, trackSizes, getTrackSize);
1018 return list;
1019 }
1020
1021 // Add the line names and track sizes that precede the auto repeat().
1022 int autoRepeatInsertionPoint = std::clamp<int>(isRowAxis ? style.gridAutoRepeatColumnsInsertionPoint() : style.gridAutoRepeatRowsInsertionPoint(), 0, trackSizes.size());
1023 populateGridTrackList(list.get(), collector, trackSizes, getTrackSize, 0, autoRepeatInsertionPoint);
1024
1025 // Add a CSSGridAutoRepeatValue with the contents of the auto repeat().
1026 AutoRepeatType autoRepeatType = isRowAxis ? style.gridAutoRepeatColumnsType() : style.gridAutoRepeatRowsType();
1027 auto repeatedValues = CSSGridAutoRepeatValue::create(autoRepeatType == AutoRepeatType::Fill ? CSSValueAutoFill : CSSValueAutoFit);
1028 OrderedNamedLinesCollectorInsideRepeat repeatCollector(style, isRowAxis);
1029 populateGridTrackList(repeatedValues.get(), repeatCollector, autoRepeatTrackSizes, getTrackSize);
1030 list->append(repeatedValues.get());
1031
1032 // Add the line names and track sizes that follow the auto repeat().
1033 populateGridTrackList(list.get(), collector, trackSizes, getTrackSize, autoRepeatInsertionPoint, trackSizes.size(), 1);
1034 return list;
1035}

1037static Ref<CSSValue> valueForGridPosition(const GridPosition& position)
1038{
1039 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1040 if (position.isAuto())
1041 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
1042
1043 if (position.isNamedGridArea())
1044 return cssValuePool.createCustomIdent(position.namedGridLine());
1045
1046 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1047 if (position.isSpan()) {
1048 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueSpan));
1049 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(position.spanPosition(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
1050 } else
1051 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(position.integerPosition(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
1052
1053 if (!position.namedGridLine().isNull())
1054 list->append(cssValuePool.createCustomIdent(position.namedGridLine()));
1055 return list;
1056}

1058static Ref<CSSValue> createTransitionPropertyValue(const Animation& animation)
1059{
1060 switch (animation.property().mode) {
1061 case Animation::TransitionMode::None:
1062 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1063 case Animation::TransitionMode::All:
1064 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAll);
1065 case Animation::TransitionMode::SingleProperty:
1066 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createCustomIdent(getPropertyNameString(animation.property().id));
1067 case Animation::TransitionMode::UnknownProperty:
1068 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createCustomIdent(animation.unknownProperty());
1069 }
1070 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1071 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1072}
1073
1074static Ref<CSSValueList> transitionPropertyValue(const AnimationList* animationList)
1075{
1076 auto list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1077 if (animationList) {
1078 for (size_t i = 0; i < animationList->size(); ++i)
1079 list->append(createTransitionPropertyValue(animationList->animation(i)));
1080 } else
1081 list->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAll));
1082 return list;
1083}

1085static Ref<CSSValueList> valueForScrollSnapType(const ScrollSnapType& type)

1087 auto value = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();

1089 value->append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(CSSValueNone));
1090 else {
1091 value->append(CSSPrimitiveValue::create(type.axis));

1106
1107static Ref<CSSValue> willChangePropertyValue(const WillChangeData* willChangeData)
1108{
1109 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1110 if (!willChangeData || !willChangeData->numFeatures())
1111 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
1112
1113 auto list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1114 for (size_t i = 0; i < willChangeData->numFeatures(); ++i) {
1115 WillChangeData::FeaturePropertyPair feature = willChangeData->featureAt(i);
1116 switch (feature.first) {
1117 case WillChangeData::ScrollPosition:
1118 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueScrollPosition));
1119 break;
1120 case WillChangeData::Contents:
1121 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueContents));
1122 break;
1123 case WillChangeData::Property:
1124 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(feature.second));
1125 break;
1126 case WillChangeData::Invalid:
1127 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1128 break;
1129 }
1130 }
1131
1132 return list;
1133}

1135static inline void appendLigaturesValue(CSSValueList& list, FontVariantLigatures value, CSSValueID yesValue, CSSValueID noValue)
1136{
1137 switch (value) {
1138 case FontVariantLigatures::Normal:
1139 return;
1140 case FontVariantLigatures::No:
1141 list.append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(noValue));
1142 return;
1143 case FontVariantLigatures::Yes:
1144 list.append(CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(yesValue));
1145 return;
1146 }
1147 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1148}
1149
1150static Ref<CSSValue> fontVariantLigaturesPropertyValue(FontVariantLigatures common, FontVariantLigatures discretionary, FontVariantLigatures historical, FontVariantLigatures contextualAlternates)
1151{
1152 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1153 if (common == FontVariantLigatures::No && discretionary == FontVariantLigatures::No && historical == FontVariantLigatures::No && contextualAlternates == FontVariantLigatures::No)
1154 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1155 if (common == FontVariantLigatures::Normal && discretionary == FontVariantLigatures::Normal && historical == FontVariantLigatures::Normal && contextualAlternates == FontVariantLigatures::Normal)
1156 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
1157
1158 auto valueList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1159 appendLigaturesValue(valueList, common, CSSValueCommonLigatures, CSSValueNoCommonLigatures);
1160 appendLigaturesValue(valueList, discretionary, CSSValueDiscretionaryLigatures, CSSValueNoDiscretionaryLigatures);
1161 appendLigaturesValue(valueList, historical, CSSValueHistoricalLigatures, CSSValueNoHistoricalLigatures);
1162 appendLigaturesValue(valueList, contextualAlternates, CSSValueContextual, CSSValueNoContextual);
1163 return valueList;
1164}
1165
1166static Ref<CSSValue> fontVariantPositionPropertyValue(FontVariantPosition position)
1167{
1168 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1169 CSSValueID valueID = CSSValueNormal;
1170 switch (position) {
1171 case FontVariantPosition::Normal:
1172 break;
1173 case FontVariantPosition::Subscript:
1174 valueID = CSSValueSub;
1175 break;
1176 case FontVariantPosition::Superscript:
1177 valueID = CSSValueSuper;
1178 break;
1179 }
1180 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(valueID);
1181}

1212static Ref<CSSValue> fontVariantNumericPropertyValue(FontVariantNumericFigure figure, FontVariantNumericSpacing spacing, FontVariantNumericFraction fraction, FontVariantNumericOrdinal ordinal, FontVariantNumericSlashedZero slashedZero)
1213{
1214 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1215 if (figure == FontVariantNumericFigure::Normal && spacing == FontVariantNumericSpacing::Normal && fraction == FontVariantNumericFraction::Normal && ordinal == FontVariantNumericOrdinal::Normal && slashedZero == FontVariantNumericSlashedZero::Normal)
1216 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
1217
1218 auto valueList = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1219 switch (figure) {
1220 case FontVariantNumericFigure::Normal:
1221 break;
1222 case FontVariantNumericFigure::LiningNumbers:
1223 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLiningNums));
1224 break;
1225 case FontVariantNumericFigure::OldStyleNumbers:
1226 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueOldstyleNums));
1227 break;
1228 }
1229
1230 switch (spacing) {
1231 case FontVariantNumericSpacing::Normal:
1232 break;
1233 case FontVariantNumericSpacing::ProportionalNumbers:
1234 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueProportionalNums));
1235 break;
1236 case FontVariantNumericSpacing::TabularNumbers:
1237 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueTabularNums));
1238 break;
1239 }
1240
1241 switch (fraction) {
1242 case FontVariantNumericFraction::Normal:
1243 break;
1244 case FontVariantNumericFraction::DiagonalFractions:
1245 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueDiagonalFractions));
1246 break;
1247 case FontVariantNumericFraction::StackedFractions:
1248 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueStackedFractions));
1249 break;
1250 }
1251
1252 if (ordinal == FontVariantNumericOrdinal::Yes)
1253 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueOrdinal));
1254 if (slashedZero == FontVariantNumericSlashedZero::Yes)
1255 valueList->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueSlashedZero));
1256
1257 return valueList;
1258}

1321static Ref<CSSValueList> delayValue(const AnimationList* animationList)
1322{
1323 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1324 auto list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1325 if (animationList) {
1326 for (size_t i = 0; i < animationList->size(); ++i)
1327 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(animationList->animation(i).delay(), CSSUnitType::CSS_S));
1328 } else {
1329 // Note that initialAnimationDelay() is used for both transitions and animations
1330 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(Animation::initialDelay(), CSSUnitType::CSS_S));
1331 }
1332 return list;
1333}

1348
1349static Ref<CSSValue> createTimingFunctionValue(const TimingFunction& timingFunction)
1350{
1351 switch (timingFunction.type()) {
1352 case TimingFunction::CubicBezierFunction: {
1353 auto& function = downcast<CubicBezierTimingFunction>(timingFunction);
1354 if (function.timingFunctionPreset() != CubicBezierTimingFunction::Custom) {
1355 CSSValueID valueId = CSSValueInvalid;
1356 switch (function.timingFunctionPreset()) {
1357 case CubicBezierTimingFunction::Ease:
1358 valueId = CSSValueEase;
1359 break;
1360 case CubicBezierTimingFunction::EaseIn:
1361 valueId = CSSValueEaseIn;
1362 break;
1363 case CubicBezierTimingFunction::EaseOut:
1364 valueId = CSSValueEaseOut;
1365 break;
1366 default:
1367 ASSERT(function.timingFunctionPreset() == CubicBezierTimingFunction::EaseInOut);
1368 valueId = CSSValueEaseInOut;
1369 break;
1370 }
1371 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(valueId);
1372 }
1373 return CSSCubicBezierTimingFunctionValue::create(function.x1(), function.y1(), function.x2(), function.y2());
1374 }
1375 case TimingFunction::StepsFunction: {
1376 auto& function = downcast<StepsTimingFunction>(timingFunction);
1377 return CSSStepsTimingFunctionValue::create(function.numberOfSteps(), function.stepPosition());
1378 }
1379 case TimingFunction::SpringFunction: {
1380 auto& function = downcast<SpringTimingFunction>(timingFunction);
1381 return CSSSpringTimingFunctionValue::create(function.mass(), function.stiffness(), function.damping(), function.initialVelocity());
1382 }
1383 default:
1384 ASSERT(timingFunction.type() == TimingFunction::LinearFunction);
1385 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLinear);
1386 }
1387}
1388
1389static Ref<CSSValueList> timingFunctionValue(const AnimationList* animationList)
1390{
1391 auto list = CSSValueList::createCommaSeparated();
1392 if (animationList) {
1393 for (size_t i = 0; i < animationList->size(); ++i)
1394 list->append(createTimingFunctionValue(*animationList->animation(i).timingFunction()));
1395 } else
1396 // Note that initialAnimationTimingFunction() is used for both transitions and animations
1397 list->append(createTimingFunctionValue(Animation::initialTimingFunction()));
1398 return list;
1399}

1409{

1411 return nullptr;

1431CSSComputedStyleDeclaration::CSSComputedStyleDeclaration(Element& element, bool allowVisitedStyle, StringView pseudoElementName)
1432 : m_element(element)
1433 , m_allowVisitedStyle(allowVisitedStyle)
1434{
1435 StringView name = pseudoElementName;
1436 if (name.startsWith(':'))
1437 name = name.substring(1);

1439 name = name.substring(1);

1441}

1462String CSSComputedStyleDeclaration::cssText() const
1463{
1464 StringBuilder result;
1465 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numComputedPropertyIDs; i++) {
1466 if (i)
1467 result.append(' ');
1468 result.append(getPropertyName(computedPropertyIDs[i]), ": ", getPropertyValue(computedPropertyIDs[i]), ';');
1469 }
1470 return result.toString();
1471}

1473ExceptionOr<void> CSSComputedStyleDeclaration::setCssText(const String&)
1474{
1475 return Exception { NoModificationAllowedError };
1476}
1477
1478RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> ComputedStyleExtractor::getFontSizeCSSValuePreferringKeyword()
1479{
1480 if (!m_element)
1481 return nullptr;
1482
1483 m_element->document().updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1484
1485 auto* style = m_element->computedStyle(m_pseudoElementSpecifier);
1486 if (!style)
1487 return nullptr;
1488
1489 if (CSSValueID sizeIdentifier = style->fontDescription().keywordSizeAsIdentifier())
1490 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(sizeIdentifier);
1491
1492 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(style->fontDescription().computedSize(), *style);
1493}
1494
1495bool ComputedStyleExtractor::useFixedFontDefaultSize()
1496{
1497 if (!m_element)
1498 return false;
1499 auto* style = m_element->computedStyle(m_pseudoElementSpecifier);
1500 if (!style)
1501 return false;
1502
1503 return style->fontDescription().useFixedDefaultSize();
1504}

1506static CSSValueID identifierForFamily(const AtomString& family)
1507{
1508 if (family == cursiveFamily)
1509 return CSSValueCursive;
1510 if (family == fantasyFamily)
1511 return CSSValueFantasy;
1512 if (family == monospaceFamily)
1513 return CSSValueMonospace;
1514 if (family == pictographFamily)
1515 return CSSValueWebkitPictograph;
1516 if (family == sansSerifFamily)
1517 return CSSValueSansSerif;
1518 if (family == serifFamily)
1519 return CSSValueSerif;
1520 if (family == systemUiFamily)
1521 return CSSValueSystemUi;
1522 return CSSValueInvalid;
1523}
1524
1525static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> valueForFamily(const AtomString& family)
1526{
1527 if (CSSValueID familyIdentifier = identifierForFamily(family))
1528 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(familyIdentifier);
1529 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createFontFamilyValue(family);
1530}

1532static Ref<CSSValue> touchActionFlagsToCSSValue(OptionSet<TouchAction> touchActions)
1533{
1534 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1535
1536 if (touchActions & TouchAction::Auto)
1537 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
1538 if (touchActions & TouchAction::None)
1539 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1540 if (touchActions & TouchAction::Manipulation)
1541 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueManipulation);
1542
1543 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1544 if (touchActions & TouchAction::PanX)
1545 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValuePanX));
1546 if (touchActions & TouchAction::PanY)
1547 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValuePanY));
1548 if (touchActions & TouchAction::PinchZoom)
1549 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValuePinchZoom));
1550
1551 if (!list->length())
1552 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueAuto);
1553 return list;
1554}

1556static Ref<CSSValue> renderTextDecorationFlagsToCSSValue(OptionSet<TextDecoration> textDecoration)
1557{

1562 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueUnderline));

1566 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueLineThrough));

1569 list->append(cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueWebkitLetterpress));

1572 if (!list->length())
1573 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1574 return list;

1685static Ref<CSSValue> fillRepeatToCSSValue(FillRepeat xRepeat, FillRepeat yRepeat)
1686{
1687 // For backwards compatibility, if both values are equal, just return one of them. And
1688 // if the two values are equivalent to repeat-x or repeat-y, just return the shorthand.
1689 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1690 if (xRepeat == yRepeat)
1691 return cssValuePool.createValue(xRepeat);
1692 if (xRepeat == FillRepeat::Repeat && yRepeat == FillRepeat::NoRepeat)
1693 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRepeatX);
1694 if (xRepeat == FillRepeat::NoRepeat && yRepeat == FillRepeat::Repeat)
1695 return cssValuePool.createIdentifierValue(CSSValueRepeatY);
1696
1697 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1698 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(xRepeat));
1699 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(yRepeat));
1700 return list;
1701}

1714static Ref<CSSValue> fillSizeToCSSValue(const FillSize& fillSize, const RenderStyle& style)
1715{
1716 if (fillSize.type == FillSizeType::Contain)
1717 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueContain);
1718
1719 if (fillSize.type == FillSizeType::Cover)
1720 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueCover);
1721
1722 if (fillSize.size.height.isAuto())
1723 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(fillSize.size.width, style);
1724
1725 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1726 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(fillSize.size.width, style));
1727 list->append(zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(fillSize.size.height, style));
1728 return list;
1729}

1735
1736static Ref<CSSValueList> contentToCSSValue(const RenderStyle& style)
1737{
1738 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1739 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1740 for (auto* contentData = style.contentData(); contentData; contentData = contentData->next()) {
1741 if (is<CounterContentData>(*contentData))
1742 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<CounterContentData>(*contentData).counter().identifier(), CSSUnitType::CSS_COUNTER_NAME));
1743 else if (is<ImageContentData>(*contentData))
1744 list->append(downcast<ImageContentData>(*contentData).image().cssValue());
1745 else if (is<TextContentData>(*contentData))
1746 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(downcast<TextContentData>(*contentData).text(), CSSUnitType::CSS_STRING));
1747 }
1748 return list;
1749}
1750
1751static Ref<CSSValue> counterToCSSValue(const RenderStyle& style, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
1752{
1753 auto* map = style.counterDirectives();
1754 if (!map)
1755 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNone);
1756
1757 auto& cssValuePool = CSSValuePool::singleton();
1758 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
1759 for (auto& keyValue : *map) {
1760 list->append(cssValuePool.createCustomIdent(keyValue.key));
1761 double number = (propertyID == CSSPropertyCounterIncrement ? keyValue.value.incrementValue : keyValue.value.resetValue).value_or(0);
1762 list->append(cssValuePool.createValue(number, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER));
1763 }
1764 return list;
1765}

1771 list->append(valueForFamily(style.fontCascade().familyAt(i)));
1772 return list;

1779 return fontFamilyListFromStyle(style);

1782static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> lineHeightFromStyle(const RenderStyle& style)
1783{
1784 Length length = style.lineHeight();
1785 if (length.isNegative())
1786 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createIdentifierValue(CSSValueNormal);
1787 if (length.isPercent()) {
1788 // This is imperfect, because it doesn't include the zoom factor and the real computation
1789 // for how high to be in pixels does include things like minimum font size and the zoom factor.
1790 // On the other hand, since font-size doesn't include the zoom factor, we really can't do
1791 // that here either.
1792 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(static_cast<double>(length.percent() * style.fontDescription().computedSize()) / 100, style);
1793 }
1794 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(floatValueForLength(length, 0), style);
1795}
1796
1797static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> fontSizeFromStyle(const RenderStyle& style)
1798{
1799 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue(style.fontDescription().computedSize(), style);
1800}

2055typedef const Length& (RenderStyle::*RenderStyleLengthGetter)() const;
2056typedef LayoutUnit (RenderBoxModelObject::*RenderBoxComputedCSSValueGetter)() const;
2057
2058template<RenderStyleLengthGetter lengthGetter, RenderBoxComputedCSSValueGetter computedCSSValueGetter>
2059static RefPtr<CSSValue> zoomAdjustedPaddingOrMarginPixelValue(const RenderStyle& style, RenderObject* renderer)
2060{
2061 Length unzoomzedLength = (style.*lengthGetter)();
2062 if (!is<RenderBox>(renderer) || unzoomzedLength.isFixed())
2063 return zoomAdjustedPixelValueForLength(unzoomzedLength, style);
2064 return zoomAdjustedPixelValue((downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).*computedCSSValueGetter)(), style);
2065}

2067template<RenderStyleLengthGetter lengthGetter>
2068static bool paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent(const RenderStyle* style, RenderObject* renderer)
2069{
2070 return renderer && style && renderer->isBox() && !(style->*lengthGetter)().isFixed();
2071}

2073static bool positionOffsetValueIsRendererDependent(const RenderStyle* style, RenderObject* renderer)
2074{

2078static CSSValueID convertToPageBreak(BreakBetween value)
2079{
2080 if (value == BreakBetween::Page || value == BreakBetween::LeftPage || value == BreakBetween::RightPage
2081 || value == BreakBetween::RectoPage || value == BreakBetween::VersoPage)
2082 return CSSValueAlways; // CSS 2.1 allows us to map these to always.
2083 if (value == BreakBetween::Avoid || value == BreakBetween::AvoidPage)
2084 return CSSValueAvoid;
2085 return CSSValueAuto;
2086}

2093 return CSSValueAvoid;

2115
2116static bool isLayoutDependent(CSSPropertyID propertyID, const RenderStyle* style, RenderObject* renderer)
2117{
2118 switch (propertyID) {
2119 case CSSPropertyTop:
2120 case CSSPropertyBottom:
2121 case CSSPropertyLeft:
2122 case CSSPropertyRight:
2123 case CSSPropertyInsetBlockStart:
2124 case CSSPropertyInsetBlockEnd:
2125 case CSSPropertyInsetInlineStart:
2126 case CSSPropertyInsetInlineEnd:
2127 return positionOffsetValueIsRendererDependent(style, renderer);
2128 case CSSPropertyWidth:
2129 case CSSPropertyHeight:
2130 case CSSPropertyInlineSize:
2131 case CSSPropertyBlockSize:
2132 return renderer && !renderer->isRenderSVGModelObject() && !isNonReplacedInline(*renderer);
2133 case CSSPropertyPerspectiveOrigin:
2134 case CSSPropertyTransformOrigin:
2135 case CSSPropertyTransform:
2136 case CSSPropertyFilter: // Why are filters layout-dependent?
2137#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
2138 case CSSPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter: // Ditto for backdrop-filter.
2139#endif
2140 return true;
2141 case CSSPropertyMargin: {
2142 if (!renderer || !renderer->isBox())
2143 return false;
2144 return !(style && style->marginTop().isFixed() && style->marginRight().isFixed()
2145 && style->marginBottom().isFixed() && style->marginLeft().isFixed());
2146 }
2147 case CSSPropertyMarginTop:
2148 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::marginTop>(style, renderer);
2149 case CSSPropertyMarginRight:
2150 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::marginRight>(style, renderer);
2151 case CSSPropertyMarginBottom:
2152 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::marginBottom>(style, renderer);
2153 case CSSPropertyMarginLeft:
2154 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::marginLeft>(style, renderer);
2155 case CSSPropertyPadding: {
2156 if (!renderer || !renderer->isBox())
2157 return false;
2158 return !(style && style->paddingTop().isFixed() && style->paddingRight().isFixed()
2159 && style->paddingBottom().isFixed() && style->paddingLeft().isFixed());
2160 }
2161 case CSSPropertyPaddingTop:
2162 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::paddingTop>(style, renderer);
2163 case CSSPropertyPaddingRight:
2164 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::paddingRight>(style, renderer);
2165 case CSSPropertyPaddingBottom:
2166 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::paddingBottom>(style, renderer);
2167 case CSSPropertyPaddingLeft:
2168 return paddingOrMarginIsRendererDependent<&RenderStyle::paddingLeft>(style, renderer);
2169 case CSSPropertyGridTemplateColumns:
2170 case CSSPropertyGridTemplateRows:
2171 case CSSPropertyGridTemplate:
2172 case CSSPropertyGrid:
2173 return renderer && renderer->isRenderGrid();
2174 default:
2175 return false;
2176 }
2177}

2179Element* ComputedStyleExtractor::styledElement() const
2180{
2181 if (!m_element)
2182 return nullptr;
2183 PseudoElement* pseudoElement;
2184 if (m_pseudoElementSpecifier == PseudoId::Before && (pseudoElement = m_element->beforePseudoElement()))
2185 return pseudoElement;
2186 if (m_pseudoElementSpecifier == PseudoId::After && (pseudoElement = m_element->afterPseudoElement()))
2187 return pseudoElement;
2188 return m_element.get();
2189}

2191RenderElement* ComputedStyleExtractor::styledRenderer() const
2192{
2193 auto* element = styledElement();
2194 if (!element)
2195 return nullptr;
2196 if (m_pseudoElementSpecifier != PseudoId::None && element == m_element.get())
2197 return nullptr;
2198 if (element->hasDisplayContents())
2199 return nullptr;
2200 return element->renderer();
2201}

2208 case CSSPropertyJustifySelf:
2209 case CSSPropertyJustifyItems:
2210 // FIXME: In StyleResolver::adjustRenderStyle z-index is adjusted based on the parent display property for grid/flex.
2211 case CSSPropertyZIndex:

2218static bool nonInheritedColorPropertyHasValueCurrentColor(CSSPropertyID propertyID, const RenderStyle* style)
2219{

2221 return false;
2222
2223 if (!style)
2224 return true;

2229// In CSS 2.1 the returned object should actually contain the "used values"

2232// See;

2250
2251static inline bool hasValidStyleForProperty(Element& element, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
2252{
2253 if (element.styleValidity() != Style::Validity::Valid)
2254 return false;
2255 if (element.document().hasPendingFullStyleRebuild())
2256 return false;
2257 if (!element.document().childNeedsStyleRecalc())
2258 return true;
2259
2260 bool isInherited = CSSProperty::isInheritedProperty(propertyID) || isImplicitlyInheritedGridOrFlexProperty(propertyID);
2261 bool maybeExplicitlyInherited = !isInherited;
2262
2263 const auto* currentElement = &element;
2264 for (auto& ancestor : composedTreeAncestors(element)) {
2265 if (ancestor.styleValidity() >= Style::Validity::SubtreeInvalid)
2266 return false;
2267
2268 if (maybeExplicitlyInherited) {
2269 auto* style = currentElement->renderStyle();
2270 // While most color properties are not inherited, the value 'currentcolor' resolves to the value of the inherited 'color' property.
2271 if (nonInheritedColorPropertyHasValueCurrentColor(propertyID, style))
2272 isInherited = true;
2273
2274 maybeExplicitlyInherited = !style || style->hasExplicitlyInheritedProperties();
2275 }
2276
2277 if ((isInherited || maybeExplicitlyInherited) && ancestor.styleValidity() == Style::Validity::ElementInvalid)
2278 return false;
2279
2280 if (ancestor.directChildNeedsStyleRecalc() && currentElement->styleIsAffectedByPreviousSibling())
2281 return false;
2282
2283 currentElement = &ancestor;
2284 }
2285
2286 return true;
2287}
2288
2289static bool updateStyleIfNeededForProperty(Element& element, CSSPropertyID propertyID)
2290{
2291 auto& document = element.document();
2292
2293 document.styleScope().flushPendingUpdate();
2294
2295 auto hasValidStyle = [&] {
2296 auto shorthand = shorthandForProperty(propertyID);
2297 if (shorthand.length()) {
2298 for (auto longhand : shorthand) {
2299 if (!hasValidStyleForProperty(element, longhand))
2300 return false;
2301 }
2302 return true;
2303 }
2304 return hasValidStyleForProperty(element, propertyID);
2305 }();
2306
2307 if (hasValidStyle)
2308 return false;
2309
2310 document.updateStyleIfNeeded();
2311 return true;
2312}

2314static inline const RenderStyle* computeRenderStyleForProperty(Element& element, PseudoId pseudoElementSpecifier, CSSPropertyID propertyID, std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle>& ownedStyle)
2315{
2316 auto* renderer = element.renderer();
2317
2318 if (renderer && renderer->isComposited() && CSSPropertyAnimation::animationOfPropertyIsAccelerated(propertyID)) {
2319 ownedStyle = renderer->animatedStyle();
2320 if (pseudoElementSpecifier != PseudoId::None && !element.isPseudoElement()) {
2321 // FIXME: This cached pseudo style will only exist if the animation has been run at least once.
2322 return ownedStyle->getCachedPseudoStyle(pseudoElementSpecifier);
2323 }
2324 return ownedStyle.get();
2325 }
2326
2327 return element.computedStyle(element.isPseudoElement() ? PseudoId::None : pseudoElementSpecifier);
2328}
